9. Bc4 { Don't get mated!  9.Bb5??  Qa5+  picks up a free bishop. } 9... Be6
{ Answering the mate threat and developing a piece with tempo. } 10. Qd3
{ 10.Qe4??  d5  would cost White a piece. } 10... Nb4
{ Continuing to play with the initiative. } 11. Bb5+ Kf8
{ The best way to get out of check. We lose castling rights, but the bishop is stranded on b5. }
12. Qe2 Nxc2+ { A little trick to get the pawn back. } 13. Qxc2 Qa5+ 14. Bd2
Qxb5
{ With a complex and roughly balanced position. Black has the bishop pair but has lost castling rights. At the same time, it is not easy for White to find a safe place for their king either. }
