Bb5
{ White often plays this move, trying to fight against our plan of ...Nc6. }
7... a6 { Asking the bishop about its intentions. } 8. Bxd7+ Bxd7
{ And ...Nc6 is coming next. Black has the bishop pair and a rock-solid center. One thing to keep in mind is that there is no rush to castle in this position.  Black's king is quite safe in the center. If anything, it would be easier for White to attack us on the kingside. So we can first improve the position with moves like ...Rc8 or ...Nc6-e7-f5. }
