2. d4
{ You might be wondering why the Morra and Alapin are in the same chapter. The answer is that if White goes for the Morra, we can force a transposition to the Alapin. This has two advantages:  It saves us a lot of work since we can just use our anti-Alapin repertoire. In a 100 repertoire, it's important to be economical! It annoys the crap out of the Morra players, who desperately want to sacrifice a pawn and go down in a blaze of glory. }
